Northrop Grumman Corporation Company Information


Northrop Grumman Corporation OverviewNorthrop Grumman Corporation was founded in 1939 and is headquartered in Falls Church, Virginia, in the Washington, D.C. area. This public company has nearly 70,000 employees worldwide and an annual revenue of over $25 billion.One of the top global security companies, Northrop Grumman makes some of the most advanced technology in the aerospace and defense industry. The company develops unmanned systems and cybersecurity products and solutions for both government and corporate customers around the world.Northrop Grumman Corporation Job OpportunitiesNorthrop Grumman has built a workforce composed of some of the world's top electronics, technology, and information systems professionals. The company regularly seeks additional top candidates in these fields.Engineering professionals take on conceptual design and related analysis of highly specialized aerospace and defense equipment. They also test prototypes, review designs, and produce successful components. Candidates must typically hold a master's degree in engineering, along with knowledge of a coding language and the ability to work in a collaborative environment.Pricing and contracts professionals administer and negotiate contracts and pricing agreements. They ensure that contracts meet both corporate policies and legal requirements. Candidates typically need a bachelor's degree in business administration and a predetermined level of security clearance.Assembly professionals create aerospace and defense parts and products. They manually move and adjust parts and perform tasks like sawing, riveting, and drilling. They continually monitor quality and control various elements of the assembly process. Candidates typically need a high school diploma and experience working in the field.Northrop Grumman Corporation Work CultureNorthrop Grumman maintains a commitment to fostering both product development and employee development. The company encourages its staff members to provide community service in their local areas and supports science and engineering education. Northrop Grumman also encourages a healthy work-life balance by offering competitive pay in the industry, career development initiatives, and flexible work arrangements. The company also offers an employee assistance program, employee discounts, networking opportunities, and a company-wide health and wellness program.

